auspexai-worker (0.1.8) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Daemon file logging — always writes to
    ~/.local/state/auspexai-worker/daemon.log via RotatingFileHandler
    (5 MB, 3 backups). Ensures logs are available regardless of how the
    daemon was started (systemd, headless SSH, manual foreground).
  * New `auspexai-worker logs` CLI command — tails the daemon log file.
    Supports -f (follow) and -n (line count). Install script post-install
    notice updated to reference `logs -f` instead of journalctl.
  * Install script: stop running daemon before upgrade (systemd or bare
    process via pkill). Fall back to nohup if systemd user service is
    unavailable (headless SSH).
  * __version__ now derived from importlib.metadata (single source of
    truth in pyproject.toml; no more hardcoded string to forget).
  * Install script wipes old site-packages/auspexai_worker* before pip
    reinstall to prevent stale overlay files from previous versions.

