auspexai-worker (0.1.4) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Local volunteer dashboard (§5.14 Layer B; closes the deferred
    Phase 2 "local volunteer dashboard" deliverable)
    - New module auspexai_worker/dashboard/ with FastAPI app + uvicorn
      server thread. Runs as a third daemon thread alongside heartbeat
      + assignment-poll loops. Localhost-only bind by default
      (127.0.0.1:7799); configurable via [dashboard] block in
      worker.toml or AUSPEXAI_WORKER_DASHBOARD_ENABLED env.
    - Four read-only HTML pages: Overview (identity + activity
      counters), Activity (last 50 assignment_audit rows), Receipts
      (last 50 submitted_results with status badges), Config
      (loaded WorkerConfig values).
    - Plus /api/stats JSON endpoint for future polling refresh.
    - Read-only by design — withdrawal, tier upgrades, etc. remain
      CLI-only (irreversible / sensitive operations stay where the
      volunteer must explicitly run them).
    - Server-rendered HTML, vanilla CSS, no JS framework, no build
      step. Adds fastapi + uvicorn to runtime deps.
    - Skipped on bounded --max-ticks runs (CI/test mode).
    - 9 new tests in test_dashboard.py.
  * Issue #1: /usr/local/bin/auspexai-worker symlink so the CLI is on
    $PATH for volunteer users after .deb install. Previously the
    binary lived only at /opt/auspexai-worker/bin/; the systemd unit
    used the absolute path so the daemon worked but volunteers
    running `auspexai-worker status` per the README hit "command not
    found". debian/auspexai-worker.links covers both auspexai-worker
    and auspexai-worker-runner.
  * Issue #2: friendly error when /etc/machine-id missing. The
    encrypted-file keystore needs machine-id (host-specific entropy
    that protects the key from being usable on a different host).
    Real Ubuntu/Debian hosts always have one; minimal containers /
    embedded systems do not. The error now includes the standard
    remediation (sudo systemd-machine-id-setup or kernel-random-uuid
    one-liner). Caught in CLI bootstrap to surface as a clean error
    instead of a KeystoreError traceback.

