auspexai-worker (0.1.3) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Graceful handling of HTTP 423 worker_quarantined (B3 follow-on)
    - New WorkerQuarantinedError exception subclass on
      auspexai_worker.coordinator. Raised by CoordinatorClient.
      get_assignment when the coordinator returns 423 (maintainer-
      applied pause). Carries the `quarantined_at` timestamp from
      the coordinator's error details.
    - AssignmentPoller catches it BEFORE the generic CoordinatorError
      branch and logs at INFO ("worker quarantined by maintainer at
      <ts>; will retry next tick") instead of WARNING. Quarantine is
      not an error condition — it's a maintainer-initiated state.
    - AssignmentStats gains polls_quarantined counter and
      quarantined_at timestamp. quarantined_at clears automatically
      on the first successful (200) poll after unquarantine.
    - The poller continues polling at normal cadence. No backoff
      added in v0.1.3; can revisit if the maintenance load becomes
      visible.
    - 3 new tests in test_assignment_poller.py covering: quarantine
      increments + records timestamp, unquarantine clears state,
      repeated quarantine doesn't kill the loop.

