auspexai-worker (0.1.1) UNRELEASED; urgency=high

  * Fix broken venv interpreter path (v0.1.0 ship-blocker)
    - debian/rules previously selected the build-host Python via
      `command -v python3.12`, which is PATH-dependent. On the GitHub
      Actions release runner, an earlier `uv python install 3.12` step
      prepended a uv-managed Python (`/home/runner/.local/share/uv/
      python/.../bin/python3.12`) to PATH. dh-virtualenv embedded that
      path as the venv's `executable=` in pyvenv.cfg and as the
      `bin/python3.12` symlink target. End-user hosts have no
      `/home/runner/...` directory, so the symlink dangles, the
      `auspexai-worker` shebang fails, and every install exits non-zero
      at postinst (rolled back by dpkg).
    - Fix: hardcode `/usr/bin/python3.12` (with `/usr/bin/python3.11`
      fallback) in debian/rules. Pre-Depends ensures the package is
      installed at build time, so the path is guaranteed.
    - v0.1.0 release yanked (marked pre-release on GitHub) with a
      broken-venv notice. Rekor entries for v0.1.0 signing remain
      permanent per the transparency-log property.

